<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Spider</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-30 11:52:10</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Are those sopposed to be words of wisdom?  LOL an interupted spell cost no mana.  It cost health and all your mana if you get killed.<BR>
Get all your spells interupted and see of you last long in any fight.  Playing a wizard you learn one thing fast.  No fight with a wizzard last long.  Either you or him are hitting the dirt soon.  Its great a wiz doesnt have to see his opponent.  So step and cast root right away andyou will know where you oppnent is qaz (man above) just look for the effects around you.  then run just where you barly see them and med when it wars you have time to blast and root  repeat.  you wont need or want to use step for anything but to regain distance control.  I dont care if you hav titaniam armor it wont beat the ac of distance.  Usualy 2 to 3 rounds is all my fights last.  ocasionaly 4.<BR>
<BR>
I see too may wizz fight wrong and lol thy get in ther an melee. Firts at a considerable distantce blast then root right away.  Now if you blast you are a fool and waisting mana because you will unroot you opponent.  use the root to allow you to start over.  Run, med,  when it wares blast  root.  stop this waiting so long to get back up to full mana.  If the opponent gets on you side step if you need to and get ready to root fast, becaues you realy dont know where the heck you will be.  Then regain control.  In pvp your opponent will get so discouraged he will kill himself just to keep the glory away from you.  Once I started doing this my wizard went from not much fun to a total blast.<BR>
